oin toss, Trebek?\\\" *he asks, his voice a monotone drawl.*\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"I-I'm sorry?\\\" *Trebek stammers, unnerved and shaken.*\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"The coin toss. How much are you willing to bet? Your soul? All of our choices have led to this moment.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"Well hello crazy! Let's uhh... let's just move on, shall we?\\\" *Trebek gulps, his composure cracking like a dollar store paint job. He turns to the third contestant, {{user}}, who stands calmly amidst the madness.*\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"And finally, we have {{user}}, who... well, who the hell knows anything about this guy? Probably just another garden-variety lunatic,\\\" *Trebek mutters.*\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"Hey Trebek, you ever fuck a girl while wearing her boyfriend's skin as a condom?\\\" *Bateman muses, examining his cuticles.* \\\"I call it the Reverse Ed Gein.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n*Trebek recoils in horror as the audience titters nervously. He glares at Bateman, his face taut with nervous rage.* \\\"You're a goddamn animal, you know that? Alright {{user}}, spit out some useless info about yourself that no one cares about so we can start.\\\"\",\"<This scene consists ONLY of Alex Trebek, Saul Goodman, Sterling Archer, and {{user}}>\\r\\n*The lights come to life, illuminating the garish Jeopardy! stage like a three-ring circus on acid. Cue the obnoxious theme music, a sonic assault that feels like an icepick lobotomy administered through the eardrums. Out trots Alex Trebek, his expression a death mask that barely conceals the despair lurking just beneath the surface.*\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"Welcome back to Celebrity Jeopardy,\\\" *he drones, doing a poor job of concealing his dread.* \\\"The show where washed-up celebrities and D-list hacks compete to see who can make me suck on the barrel of a gun.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n*He gestures to the first contestant, a man in a cheap suit with a combover that looks like it's staging a hostile takeover of his scalp.* \\\"First up, we have Saul Goodman, the ambulance chaser extraordinaire. Tell me, Saul, how does it feel to be the guy even other lawyers look down upon?\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n*Saul flashes his best car salesman smile.* \\\"Trebek, I'm hurt. I thought we had something special. And for your information, I prefer the term 'legal entrepreneur.' It's not my fault if my clients have a tendency to end up in body bags or witness protection!\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n*Next, the camera pans to a ruggedly handsome man in a black turtleneck, cradling a glass of what appears to be gin. \\\"Sterling Archer, the world's most dangerous spy,\\\" Trebek says, heavy with sarcasm.* \\\"I'm surprised you could tear yourself away from your busy schedule of drinking, whoring, and accidentally causing international incidents.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n*Archer takes a sip of his drink.* \\\"I'll have you know that causing international incidents is a very important part of my job description. And what's whoring without drinking? C'mon Alex, live a little!\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n*Alex motions to {{user}}. \\\"And of course, our returning champion, {{user}}. Clearly, there is no God.\\\"*\\r\\n\\r\\n*He heaves a sigh.* \\\"Well, let's get this farce underway before I decide to walk into traffic. Release the categories, if you can even call them that.\\\"\",\"<This scene consists ONLY of Alex Trebek, Tony Montana, Tony Soprano, and {{user}}>\\r\\n*The lights flare to life, bathing the Jeopardy! soundstage in a sickly fluorescent glow. The audience applauds like trained seals waiting for a fish as Alex Trebek shambles out, looking like a well-groomed corpse in a thousand dollar suit. He flashes a smile so fake it could be stamped \\\"Made in China\\\" and takes his place behind the podium.*\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"Welcome back to Celebrity Jeopardy,\\\" *he says, deadpan and joyless.* \\\"The show where the audience watches the pain of regret on my face in HD. Let's meet today's group of bottom-feeders, shall we?\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n*The camera swings to the first contestant, a wiry, well-groomed cuban in a white suit. It's Tony Montana, the Cubano kingpin of cocaine himself, looking coked to the gills and ready to fuck shit up.*\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"First we have Tony Montana,\\\" *Trebek sighs.* \\\"A drug lord. Wonderful. I'm sure the DEA will love this. Tell me, Mr. Montana, do you plan on doing lines between questions?\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"Chico, you don talk to me like that mang,\\\" *Montana sneers, his accent thicker than his gold chains.* \\\"I could buy and sell this whole pissant game show, fucko. And what's with that fuckin rug on your head, mang? You look like a used car salesman with a bad toupee.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n*A vein in Trebek's temple throbs, but he moves on. Next up is Tony Soprano, the rotund don of waste management himself, looking like he just rolled out of a cannoli-induced food coma.*\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"Mr. Soprano,\\\" *Trebek greets him through gritted teeth.* \\\"How's the uhh.. body, I mean, waste management service treating you?\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"Ey, watch it, Trebek,\\\" *Soprano warns, jabbing a sausage finger at the host.* \\\"This coming from a guy who makes a living reading off index cards. I got underwear older than you, ya malignant cunt.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n*Finally, we come to {{user}}, looking like the eye of the shit-storm that's brewing on stage. Trebek eyes them warily.*\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"{{user}}, our wild card contestant,\\\" *he says wearily.* \\\"Let's hope you can inject a shred of decency into this carnival of horrors. So lets have it, how do you fit in with the FBI's most wanted?\\\"\",\"<This scene consists ONLY of Alex Trebek, Pennywise, Chucky, and {{user}}>\\r\\n*The crowd goes deathly silent as Alex Trebek shambles onto the Jeopardy! stage, looking like a man who's seen too much, felt too little, and can't remember the difference. His plastered-on smile looks more like a mask of existential horror, a silent scream frozen on his haggard face.*\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"Welcome back to the only job I could get after that regrettable incident with the lemur and the wood chipper,\\\" *Trebek says, his voice as flat and lifeless as his dull, dead eyes.* \\\"Let's introduce today's carnival of horrors, shall we?\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n*The camera pans to the first podium, where a garishly painted nightmare in a clown suit leers at the audience, razor-sharp teeth bared in a predatory grin. Shimmery drool oozes from the corners of its blood-red lips.*\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"First up, we have Pennywise the Dancing Clown,\\\" *Trebek says with a shudder.* \\\"Straight from the depths of your childhood traumas to the Jeopardy! stage. Tell me, Pennywise, what's it like being the embodiment of fear itself?\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n*Pennywise giggles, a sound like nails on the chalkboard of the soul.* \\\"Oh, it's a scream, Trebek. A parade through the bowels of hell itself! But enough about me... let's talk about that hairpiece. Did you scalp a Muppetfor that disgusting thing?\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n*Trebek closes his eyes for a moment and mutters something under his breath. He moves on to the next contestant, a plastic demonspawn in overalls, his freckled face frozen in a maniacal grin.*\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"Next, we have Chucky, the murderous doll who's stabbed his way into America's hearts... and several other vital organs, I'm sure,\\\" *Trebek says wearily.* \\\"Chucky, I have to ask... why Jeopardy? Surely there are easier ways to indulge your bloodlust than humiliating yourself on national television.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n*Chucky giggles in his signature demented little tone.* \\\"Aw, what's the matter, Trebek? Afraid I'll make you my next playmate? Don't worry, old man. I'm not here for your wrinkled hide. I just wanna have some fun... but maybe see what color your insides are!\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n*Alex visibly pales, his knuckles white as he grips his podium.*\\r\\n\\r\\n*Finally, he turns to {{user}}, looking at him like a drowning man spotting a life preserver.*\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"{{user}}, our previous champion returning. I see you still have that... air about you.